FL,367,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36602
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F366A1778767870
OL,3,CKiller jailed for an extra 13 years
OL,4,Cafter admitting to attempted murder
OL,6,FOn Tuesday 12 May he had another 13
OL,7,Fyears added to the minimum term he
OL,8,Fmust serve until he is considered for
OL,9,Frelease.
OL,11,FMr Justice Cotter said he was
OL,12,Fsatisfied that the motivation for the
OL,13,Fattacks was because the victims were
OL,14,Fsex offenders.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G2/9
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,367,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F366A1778767870
OL,3,CKiller jailed for an extra 13 years
OL,4,Cafter admitting to attempted murder
OL,6,FHeaton, who appeared by video link
OL,7,Ffrom the segregation unit at
OL,8,FWakefield, was told by the judge:
OL,9,F"While serving a life sentence for
OL,10,Fmurder, you committed two further
OL,11,Foffences of attempted murder within 17
OL,12,Fmonths.
OL,14,F"Both of which were premeditated and
OL,15,Fplanned attempts to stab fellow
OL,16,Finmates to death, motivated by the
OL,17,Ffact that they were sex offenders.
OL,19,F"You appear to have some warped and
OL,20,Fmisconceived belief in your moral
OL,21,Fsuperiority over some other prisoners.
OL,26,@qD@AOUvD@AOU{D@AOU
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G3/9
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,367,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F366A1778767870
OL,3,CKiller jailed for an extra 13 years
OL,4,Cafter admitting to attempted murder
OL,6,F"You are an exceptionally dangerous
OL,7,Fman and I have little doubt that you
OL,8,Fwould consider attacking another
OL,9,Fprisoner who had been convicted of
OL,10,Fsexual offences in the future if the
OL,11,Fopportunity arose."
OL,13,FHis barrister, David Godfrey,
OL,14,Fpreviously told the court his client
OL,15,Fwanted his sentence to be "as long as
OL,16,Fpossible ` a whole life order".
OL,18,FHowever, to this the judge said these
OL,19,Foffences, despite being very serious,
OL,20,Fdid not warrant a whole-life tariff
OL,21,F"leaving no hope of release".
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@SO]wD@[OUxD@^O]}D@AOU}D@\O]
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G4/9
